INTERNAL: Add default theme options to tables

Source: R/utils.R
finalize_tbl.Rd

finalize_tbl() is used internally to complete the table creation process. This function creates a flextable object and adds theme choices and size specifications.

Usage

finalize_tbl(table, digits, striped = TRUE, caption = NULL, na_str = "NA")

Arguments

table

A dataframe (to be coerced to a flextable object)

digits

The number of digits to round double columns to

striped

Should the table be striped alternating colors (white/grey)? Defaults to TRUE.

caption

The table caption. Defaults to NULL (or no caption).

na_str

What string should appear when an NA appears? Defaults to "NA".

Value

An object of class flextable.

Examples

finalize_tbl(mtcars, digits = 3, caption = "The mtcars Dataset")
